wikipedia_page.main: Henry Floyd (born 2 April 1793 in Bengal; died 4 March 1868 in Hyde Park, London) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) who was active in the 1810s. He is recorded in one match in 1817, totalling 1 run with a highest score of 1.
